{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-post-template-tsx","path":"/poste/understanding-the-minimum-effect-of-interest/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"213e09e8-860c-5576-9726-5a151ceda08c","html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/54b023bdda7dc0811adeb392d2c65fd8/4b190/parameter-of-interest.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 50%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/54b023bdda7dc0811adeb392d2c65fd8/8ac56/parameter-of-interest.webp 240w,\n/static/54b023bdda7dc0811adeb392d2c65fd8/d3be9/parameter-of-interest.webp 480w,\n/static/54b023bdda7dc0811adeb392d2c65fd8/d00b9/parameter-of-interest.webp 800w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/54b023bdda7dc0811adeb392d2c65fd8/09b79/parameter-of-interest.jpg 240w,\n/static/54b023bdda7dc0811adeb392d2c65fd8/7cc5e/parameter-of-interest.jpg 480w,\n/static/54b023bdda7dc0811adeb392d2c65fd8/4b190/parameter-of-interest.jpg 800w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/54b023bdda7dc0811adeb392d2c65fd8/4b190/parameter-of-interest.jpg\"\n            alt=\"parameter-of-interest\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>The <strong>Minimum Effect of Interest (MEI)</strong> is a business term meaning the smallest effect that has business value. It is usually used to determine the minimum sample size needed in an experiment. When the data is collected, the effect size is calculated, and if the effect size is smaller than the MEI, the result is considered to be not practically significant.</p>\n<h2 id=\"calculating-the-minimum-effect-of-interest\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#calculating-the-minimum-effect-of-interest\" aria-label=\"calculating the minimum effect of interest permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Calculating the Minimum Effect of Interest</h2>\n<p>The formula to calculate the minimum sample size is:</p>\n<p><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">N</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msub><mi>Z</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>−</mo><mi>α</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>Z</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>−</mo><mi>β</mi></mrow></msub><msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mrow><mi>C</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><msup><mrow><mi>M</mi><mi>E</mi><mi>I</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{N} = \\frac{2(Z_{1-\\alpha/2} + Z_{1-\\beta})^{2}{CV}^{2}}{{MEI}^{2}}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6861em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">N</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.5561em;vertical-align:-0.3636em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mopen nulldelimiter\"></span><span class=\"mfrac\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.1926em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.6364em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">ME</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">I</span></span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.7908em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.8305em;margin-right:0.0714em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.5em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size3 size1 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.23em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"frac-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.5686em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span><span class=\"mopen mtight\">(</span><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">Z</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3448em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.3448em;margin-left:-0.0715em;margin-right:0.0714em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.5357em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size3 size1 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span><span class=\"mbin mtight\">−</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.0037em;\">α</span><span class=\"mord mtight\">/2</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3695em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mbin mtight\">+</span><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">Z</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3448em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.3488em;margin-left:-0.0715em;margin-right:0.0714em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.5em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size3 size1 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span><span class=\"mbin mtight\">−</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.05278em;\">β</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2901em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose mtight\"><span class=\"mclose mtight\">)</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8913em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.931em;margin-right:0.0714em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.5em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size3 size1 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">V</span></span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8913em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.931em;margin-right:0.0714em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.5em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size3 size1 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3636em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose nulldelimiter\"></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p>Where:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>N</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">N</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">N</span></span></span></span></span>: the minimum sample size</li>\n<li><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>Z</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>−</mo><mi>α</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">Z_{1-\\alpha/2}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0385em;vertical-align:-0.3552em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">Z</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3448em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5198em;margin-left:-0.0715em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span><span class=\"mbin mtight\">−</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.0037em;\">α</span><span class=\"mord mtight\">/2</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3552em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>: the Z-score for the desired confidence level</li>\n<li><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>Z</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>−</mo><mi>β</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">Z_{1-\\beta}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.9694em;vertical-align:-0.2861em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">Z</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3361em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.0715em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span><span class=\"mbin mtight\">−</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.05278em;\">β</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2861em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>: the Z-score for the desired power</li>\n<li><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>C</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">CV</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">V</span></span></span></span></span>: the coefficient of variation</li>\n<li><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>M</mi><mi>E</mi><mi>I</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">MEI</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">ME</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">I</span></span></span></span></span>: the minimum effect of interest, it’s usually set to 0.02 or 0.05</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"difference-between-minimum-effect-of-interest-and-minimum-detectable-effect\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#difference-between-minimum-effect-of-interest-and-minimum-detectable-effect\" aria-label=\"difference between minimum effect of interest and minimum detectable effect permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Difference between Minimum Effect of Interest and Minimum Detectable Effect</h2>\n<p>There’s another famous term in statistics called <strong>Minimum Detectable Effect (MDE)</strong>, which is the smallest effect that can be detected with a given sample size. MEI and MDE are similar but generally in the opposite direction. The minimal sample size is the output of the MEI, but the real sample size is the input of the MDE.</p>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/2016-09-10---Understanding-the-Minimum-Effect-of-Interest//poste/understanding-the-minimum-effect-of-interest","tagSlugs":["/tag/data-processing/","/tag/statistics/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2016-09-10T20:00:00.000Z","description":"the concept of minimum effect of interest means a minimum effect size that is considered to be of practical importance.","tags":["Data Processing","Statistics"],"title":"Understanding the Minimum Effect of Interest","socialImage":{"publicURL":"/static/54b023bdda7dc0811adeb392d2c65fd8/parameter-of-interest.jpg"}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/2016-09-10---Understanding-the-Minimum-Effect-of-Interest//poste/understanding-the-minimum-effect-of-interest"}},"staticQueryHashes":["251939775","288581551","401334301"],"slicesMap":{}}